The paper focuses on embodied computer vision for robots in unstructured environments, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper specifically addresses the problem of visual exploration, which is a sub-topic of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents empirical results and benchmarks, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
